   "source": [
    "# Useful tips\n",
    "\n",
    "The API documentation does not give credits to some useful features find in prose. Here is a non exausthive demonstartion of some of them:\n",
    "\n",
    "- [Accessing blocks](#Accessing-blocks)\n",
    "- [Plotting in Sequence](#Plotting-in-Sequence)\n",
    "- [Checking catalogs](#Checking-catalogs)\n",
    "- [Custom apertures](#Custom-apertures)\n",
    "\n",
    "In what follows we will make examples from a random set of images"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "junior-census",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-07-28T15:14:03.381234Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-07-28T15:14:03.381034Z",

     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-07-28T15:14:08.844380Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from prose import Image, Sequence\n",
    "\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "images = [Image(data=np.random.randn(100,100)) for i in range(5)]"
   ]
  },

   "id": "previous-approval",

   "source": [
    "## Accessing blocks\n",
    "\n",
    "When a `Sequence` is defined there are few ways to access its blocks. Let's define one for example"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "western-charleston",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-07-28T15:14:08.847752Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-07-28T15:14:08.847459Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-07-28T15:14:08.851474Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-07-28T15:14:08.851028Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from prose.blocks import Set, Pass, SegmentedPeaks\n",
    "\n",
    "sequence = Sequence([\n",
    "    Pass(name=\"named_block\"),\n",
    "    Set(example=True),\n",
    "    SegmentedPeaks(),\n",
    "])"
   ]
  },

   "id": "permanent-breach",

   "source": [
    "## Plotting in Sequence\n",
    "\n",
    "The `Plot` `Block` can be used to record any plotting function applied to an `Image`, like"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "dedicated-premium",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-07-28T15:14:08.866097Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-07-28T15:14:08.865914Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-07-28T15:14:09.210076Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-07-28T15:14:09.209558Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x288 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# This function plot the image, its max and an histogram of it\n",
    "def show(image):\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(8,4))\n",
    "    plt.subplot(121)\n",
    "    plt.title(\"image data\", loc=\"left\")\n",
    "    plt.imshow(image.data, origin=\"lower\", cmap=\"Greys\")\n",
    "    plt.plot(*np.unravel_index(np.argmax(image.data), image.data.shape), \"o\", \n",
    "             ms=10, fillstyle=\"none\", c=\"w\", markeredgewidth=3, label=\"max\")\n",
    "    plt.text(5, 5, image.i if hasattr(image, \"i\") else \"--\", color=\"white\", fontsize=14)\n",
    "    plt.legend()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plt.subplot(122)\n",
    "    plt.hist(image.data.flatten(), bins=100, color=\"k\")\n",
    "    plt.xlim(-5, 5)\n",
    "    plt.ylim(0, 500)\n",
    "    plt.title(\"image histogram\", loc=\"left\")\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    \n",
    "# for example\n",
    "show(images[0])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "polish-boring",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This can be used within a `Sequence` through the use of `Plot` to create a video/gif of it"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "worth-potato",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-07-28T15:14:09.212915Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-07-28T15:14:09.212744Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-07-28T15:14:10.330591Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-07-28T15:14:10.330071Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\u001b[38;5;12mRUN\u001b[0m 100%|\u001b[38;5;12m█████████████████████████████████████\u001b[0m| 5/5 [00:01<00:00,  4.89images/s]\u001b[0m\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from prose.blocks.vizualisation import PlotVideo\n",
    "\n",
    "# we define our block\n",
    "plot_block = PlotVideo(show, \"plots.gif\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# adding to the sequence and running\n",
    "sequence = Sequence([plot_block])\n",
    "sequence.run(images)"
   ]
  },

   "id": "detailed-platform",

   "source": [
    "![](plots.gif)"
   ]

   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# defining aperture(s)\n",
    "rin = 10\n",
    "rout = 20\n",
    "apertures = np.linspace(3, rin, 10) # multiple apertures\n",
    "\n",
    "obs.plot_radial_psf(0, aperture=apertures[0], rin=rin, rout=rout, n=15)"
   ]
  },
